stream
q
/Tx BMC 
q
1 1 492.3312 306.999 re
W
BT
/HeBo 9.0 Tf 0 g
2 297.999 Td
(This SAR is being filed to report suspicious activity involving Global Trade Corp, a customer of Example Community Bank, identified through an alert generated on October 4, 2023, due to unusual cash patterns and multiple day deposits. The suspicious activity was discovered between March 15, 2024, and April 15, 2024, during which the subject conducted a series of cash deposits followed by immediate wire transfers, structured to avoid Currency Transaction Reporting \(CTR\) thresholds. Specifically, five transactions were identified: on March 18, 2024, a cash deposit of $9,500 was made, followed by a wire transfer; on March 25, 2024, a deposit of $9,800 occurred with an immediate wire transfer; on April 2, 2024, a deposit of $9,700 was made, again followed by a wire transfer; on April 10, 2024, a cash deposit of $9,900 was recorded with a subsequent wire transfer; and finally, on April 15, 2024, a deposit of $6,200 was made, completing the pattern. The total amount involved in these transactions was $45,100. The transactions were conducted from an account associated with the subject and involved funds transfers to multiple beneficiaries in Miami, FL. The subject has declined to explain the large cash deposits, and there is no apparent business purpose for these transactions. The bank has retained all supporting documentation, including transaction records, for five years from the date of filing. Further investigation is recommended to determine the legitimacy of these transactions and the potential for money laundering activities.) Tj
ET
Q
EMC
Q

endstream
endobj
